</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="134.[151,1437,1697,2011]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,432,1733,1759]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1979" box="[439,625,1733,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sathytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[439,625,1733,1759]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Sathytes simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species of the genus known to possess simple antennae in the male.
</paragraph>
