<subSubSection pageId="134" pageNumber="135" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="134.[151,1437,1697,2011]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1805,1831]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Distribution.</emphasis>
Darjeeling District, N India; Bomê County and Chagyib District (Nyingchi), 
<collectingRegion box="[1225,1309,1805,1831]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Xizang</collectingRegion>
, SW China (
<figureCitation box="[159,264,1841,1867]" captionStart="FIGURE 84" captionStartId="186.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,181,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-19@186.[151,1437,181,1848]" captionTargetPageId="186" captionText="FIGURE 84. Distribution of Tibetan Batrisini. A. Sathytes magnus Yin &amp; Li (circle), S. panzhaohuii Yin &amp; Shen (triangle) and S. pengzhongi sp. nov. (square). B. S. proclivis sp. nov. (circle), S. pseudograndis sp. nov. (triangle) and S. simplex Löbl (square). C. S. sympatricus sp. nov. (circle), S. transversus Yin &amp; Shen (triangle) and S. virupaksa sp. nov. (square)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6340938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6340938/files/figure.png" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Figs 84B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[274,360,1841,1867]" captionStart="FIGURE 97" captionStartId="199.[151,250,1355,1379]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,181,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-15@199.[151,1437,181,1332]" captionTargetPageId="199" captionText="FIGURE 97. Environment of and collecting sites at Nyingchi area. A. Sign of Yigong Tea Farm (ƌŭē厂). B. Forest near Yigong. C. Forest at Pailong Township (ḦË乡). D. Forest near Tongmai Town (ȃ9W)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6340967" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6340967/files/figure.png" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">97A–C</figureCitation>
). By discovering the new populations in China, the known range of this species extends considerably for some 
<quantity box="[312,397,1877,1904]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" unit="km" value="750.0">750 km</quantity>
to the northeast. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[591,959,1877,1903]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
New country record for 
<collectingCountry box="[879,954,1877,1903]" name="China" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">China</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="135" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="134.[151,1437,1697,2011]" lastBlockId="135.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="135" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1913,1939]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</emphasis>
Even when adjusted to a same angle, the aedeagi of the populations from 
<collectingCountry box="[1170,1237,1913,1939]" name="China" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">China</collectingCountry>
appear to be less protuberant at the apical margin than is shown in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lobl I." box="[699,828,1949,1975]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="285 - 307" refId="ref143858" refString="Lobl I. (1979) Revision du genre Sathytes Westwood (Coleoptera, Pselaphidae). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 86, 285 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 82294" type="journal article" year="1979">Löbl (1979</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 35). However, this difference could be reasonably fall into the range of intraspecific variation. The measurements of the body segments show no significant difference from those of specimens from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[606,667,151,177]" name="India" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">India</collectingCountry>
. The populations of 
<collectingCountry box="[903,970,151,177]" name="China" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">China</collectingCountry>
are temporarily identified as conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1979" box="[208,323,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sathytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[208,222,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[237,323,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A direct comparison with the 
<typeStatus box="[669,767,187,213]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">holotype</typeStatus>
in the future is desired, since in many cases this is the only means to distinguish morphologically similar species within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1870" box="[832,925,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sathytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[832,925,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">Sathytes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
